5. Why humans developed “scent-like” thinking

The brain evolved to detect weak signals in noisy environments.

Predators, social deception, environmental change — these often show subtle signs before they’re obvious.

So the brain developed fast pattern detectors that trigger:
	•	curiosity
	•	suspicion
	•	insight

before the reasoning chain becomes explicit.

